ingredients.Name: Skinless salmon filet cut into bite sized cubes

directions.Direction: Cut your salmon into bite-sized pieces
season well with Dano’s Cheesoning
Spray your salmon with Olive Oil spray generously.
Air fry your salmon on 385 for 8-10 minutes flipping halfway through, to ensure it is crispy on all sides.
Heat your butter in a pan on low to medium heat, and cook down garlic and parsley for 2 minutes or until aromatic. add in Cheesoning.
Pour sauce onto your Salmon Bites and enjoy!

ingredients.Name: Cajun Seasoning of your liking (Tony’s is my preferred choice)
Cayenne Pepper (Omit this if you do not like spicy)

directions.Direction: Season chicken wings well, and mix with olive oil.
Pre-Heat your Ninja Kitchen Woodfire Grill to 245, add in your Woodfire Grill Chips.
Once heated, add your chicken wings, allowing enough space in between each one.
Fully cook for 2 hours, flipping halfway through. Cooking low and slow will ensure they are still nice and juicy when it’s finished.
Enjoy once done!
Preheat your oven to 400°F
Season your chicken thoroughly with the seasonings listed, add corn starch (this will make it crispy), and mix everything very well.
Bake for 40 minutes, flipping the wings halfway through cooking time.
Heat a pan on low to medium heat, add butter, honey, brown sugar, and Franks Red Hot Buffalo Wing sauce.
Once the chicken is cooked, toss the wings in the sauce and enjoy!

ingredients.Name: Ancho Chili's or Ancho Chili Seasoning (I used the seasoning)

directions.Direction: Start by prepping your ingredients, this consist of cutting your Guajillo chili's open and removing the seeds to prevent extra spice. Please be careful and use gloves if needed.
Slice your tomato and onion into large pieces as well.
Slice your chuck roast into large pieces and season with salt and pepper. (Cutting the meat will just help with cooking time).
Heat a large pot, once pot has heated, add your olive oil and allow that to heat as well.
Add your chuck roast to the pot and allow it to sear on each side for about 5 minutes on each side.
After searing add in your tomato, garlic, Guajillo chili's, can of chipotle peppers, bay leaves.
Add in your water, ancho chili powder, garlic powder, onion powder, oregano, beef bouillon, and cinnamon stick. Mix well and cover to allow to cook on a medium heat.
After 25 minutes remove your Guajillo Chili's, tomato, chipotle peppers, and garlic and place into the blender with 1 1/2 cup of the broth the beef was cooking in.
Blend until smooth and strain if necessary. Add back into the pot to cook with the meat along with 1 cup of water.
Cook for an additional 2 hours (on a medium heat), adding water if necessary. (If meat starting to be exposed and is not covered, add in some beef broth or water)
Once beef is cooked and shredding/falling apart, remove from pan and place into a bowl aside.
Add 1/2 cup of the broth made from the beef to the meat to add some moisture before shredding.
Prep in 4 different bowls, your shredded meat, chopped red onion, cheese, and cilantro.
Lay out your eggroll and place down cheese, meat, cilantro, red onion, and cheese again.
Roll egg roll from the bottom corner first, tuck in the sides half way through rolling, and then continue to roll. Use water along the edges to help seal the eggroll.
Place in HOT oil (350 degrees) and allow to cook until golden brown.
Allow to cool before serving with the broth (topped with cilantro and onion).
Serve and Enjoy!

ingredients.Name: Blend of  TBSP salt, pepper, garlic Powder

directions.Direction: Start by removing the meat from the Lobster Tail. Use Kitchen Scissors to cut through the middle of the tail, pop the shell open, and remove as much meat as you can.
Wash your lobster meat to assure all of the shell pieces have been removed.
Cut your lobster tail into bite sized pieces.
Create a seasoning blend with the seasonings listed for the easiest results.
Heat a wok on a medium to high heat, add in your olive oil and garlic herb butter.
Once butter has melted, add in your lobster meat, season generously, and allow to cook for 2 minutes.
Scoot your lobster meat to one side, and add in your shrimp. Be sure your shrimp is laid individually and not piled on top of one another. To ensure the best cook on both sides.
Cook those both for an additional 4-5 minutes. Once your seafood is finished, remove it from the pan, and set it aside.
In the same pan, add in sesame oil, and turn your heat down to a medium/low setting.
Add in your garlic, onion, and green onions, cook until aromatic for about 2 minutes total.
Add in your day old rice, or you can get some steamed white rice from your local Chinese Food Restaurant, and be sure all of the clumps are removed from the rice.
Turn the heat in your pan back up to a medium high, add in your frozen peas and carrots, and cook down for 3 minutes.
Add in your soy sauce, and sprinkle in some of your seasoning blend as well. Mix well until combined for 2/3 minutes, watch your heat and make sure you are not burning your rice.
Push your rice to the side, add in your eggs, cook those down, and mix well with your rice.
Add in the seafood, well combined! Garnish with some green onion, and add in Yum Yum sauce if you would like! Enjoy!
Cut your salmon into bite sized pieces, be sure to make sure they are the same size to give a more uniform cook. Slice your veggies, if you like them diced that works as well.
Create your seasoning blend, use 1 TBSP of all the seasonings listed above. This is going to be used on everything so mix well and set aside.
In seperate bowls season your salmon and shrimp, drizzle with olive oil.
Heat a pan with olive oil, once heated, add in your veggies and cook until they are done to your liking. Once finished remove from pan.
Once removed add in your salmon bites and cook for about 3 minutes on each side. Be sure to flip them, once finished, remove them from the pan.
Add in your shrimp, cook for about 3 minutes on each side. Remove from pan.
Add in your day old rice and be sure to get clumps out of the rice. Season your rice to your liking, mix it well.
Mix room temparture butter and garlic very well and add into your rice.
Once its seasoned well add in your veggies, shrimp, and salmon. Cook your sauce on a medium to high heat for about 3-4 minutes.
Top your rice with the sauce, sprinkle a little of your seasoning blend, and parsley for garnish. Enjoy!

Creator: brisheat
Name: Cajun Salmon & Shrimp Fried Rice Creamy Sauce

directions.Direction: Start by washing your rice until the water runs clear, this helps me personally.
In a pot add in your olive oil and begin to heat on a medium to low heat setting, add in 1 TSP of salt, and allow to heat for 2-3 minutes.
Add in your rice, allow the rice to toast in the oil/salt for about 2 minutes.
Add in your water, allow your rice to come to a slight boil for 5 minutes before turning the heat down to a low.
Cover your rice, and cook on a low setting until rice is nice and fluffy.
Once rice has finished, uncover, and fluff through your rice with a fork.
Serve with your favorite entree and enjoy!
Start by preparing all of your veggies, dice bell peppers and onions. Get seasonings out and accesible.
In a pan add olive oil and allow to heat on a medium high heat before adding in your ground beef.
Cook ground beef down and break into smaller pieces with spatula or meat smasher.
Season lighlty with seasonings listed and add in your bell peppers & onions. Allow to cook together for 3-4 minutes.
Drain meat and veggies once it has finished cooking. Add back into your pan once finished.
Season again lightly, before adding in your washed rice.
Allow rice to toast in the heat of the pan and get the flavor of the meat & veggies for about 2-3 minutes.
Add in your chicken broth and season lightly again, add your bay leaves, cover with a top, and allow to cook for 15-20 minutes.
Once finished, fluff your rice with your fork and give it a nice taste!
Enjoy!

ingredients.Name: 8 oz blocks of Colby & Monterey Jack Cheese
blocks 8 oz (or a 16 oz)bag of Sharp Cheddar Cheese

directions.Direction: Grate all of your cheese for best results, use an electric or hand shredder for easiest results.
Boil your water for your elbow noodles, add in 3 TBSP of Chicken bouillon. Preheat your oven to 375
Once boiling, add in Elbow noodles, and cook until aldente (mostly done). Be sure to mix your noodles while they are cooking to prevent them from sticking to one another.
While your noodles are cooking, add shredded  cheeses into a bowl and mix until well combined.
Heat your heavy whipping cream and slowly add in your cheese, while continously mixing into the heavy whipping cream.
Do not add all of your cheese into the heavy whipping cream, you will need about 2 cups to cover the top of the noodles.
Strain your noodles, and rinse with cool water to prevent sticking. Add in your cheese mixture and season to taste with seasonings listed above.
Pour into a pan, and cover with cheese, paprika, and parsley.
Bake for 10- 15 minutes or until golden brown on the top. Remove from oven once finished, allow to cool for 10 minutes.
Pair with your favoirte entree and enjoy!
Dice your potatoes into bigger chunks to help with cooking time.
Add potatoes and chicken bouillon to a pot of boiling water on medium to high heat.
After 20 minutes or once the potatoes are softened, drain water and mash your potatoes well.
Add in heavy whipping cream and mix well with mashed potatoes.
Add in your seasonings, butter, and chives.
Serve and Enjoy!

ingredients.Name: of Collard Greens, cleaned and cut

directions.Direction: Be sure to start with cleaned greens, I like to soak in water & apple cider vinegar. Wash a few times until water runs clear, this will take a while. Pull your greens off of the large stem in the middle and roll 2/3 leaves together at a time. Slice so you have small shred-like pieces to use for your greens.
In a Dutch oven or pot, heat your butter and add in onion. Once aromatic, add garlic. Be sure to cook on a medium to low heat to avoid burning.

Add in smoked turkey and pour 4-6 cups of water or until turkey wings are covered, add in chicken bouillon and allow to cook on medium heat and cook for 25 minutes or until meat is tender for shreading.
Remove turkey wings, and shred getting as much meat off as possible.
Add collard greens and cover. Cook for additional 25 minutes.
Season greens to your desired taste and allow to cook on simmer of an additional 45 minutes to an hour.
Add a small cap full of apple cider vinegar into the pot and mix into the greens.
Cook for additional 20 minutes or until greens are tender like you prefer.
Cook bacon until crisp and set aside
Heat your water and add chicken bouillon when it comes to a boil
Add in your chopped and peeled potatoes and allow to boil for 10 minutes
Add in green beans and allow to cook for 5-7 minutes. Use a fork to test tenderness of both potatoes and green beans
Add in bacon and cook on simmer for additional 5 minutes, season with salt, pepper and garlic powder
Serve and Enjoy!
Combine dry ingredients and mix well. (Cornmeal, sugar, flour, baking powder).
Add egg, milk, honey into mixture.
Butter cast iron skillet fully and pour mixture in.
Bake for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Melt 2 TBSP butter and add in honey, mix well and pour on top of cornbread.
Slice your lamb chops and clean with water and vinegar. Allow to soak for about 5-10 minutes.
Season generously with seasonings listed. Drizzle a little oil on them and mix until well combined.
In a cast iron or HexClad pan, add your grape seed oil and allow to heat on a high heat.
Once pan is nice and hot add in your lamb chops. Allow them to sear on each side for 3-4 minutes, only flipping once.
Remove from pan and cook additional lamb chops in this same oil/heated pan.
For the Sauce
Make your sauce in a bowl and mix ingredients until well combined.
Once finished, turn heat down to a medium low, add in lamb chops and the sauce.
Allow to deglaze for 2/3 minutes, and serve!
Prepare all of your veggies by slicing and dicing, place in bowl, set aside. PreHeat oven to 300 degrees.
Season your Beef Short Ribs with salt and pepper on all sides.
Heat your Dutch oven on a medium to high heat, once it has heated add in your olive oil. Allow 2 minutes for oil to become heated as well.
Once the oil is heated, add in your beef short ribs and sear for 4 minutes on each side. Ensure there is a very nice and even sear on all sides!
After searing, remove short ribs and set aside. Turn heat down to a low/medium heat.
Add carrot, onion, celery and 1/2 of your garlic head into the pan. Allow to simmer and cook for 3-4 minutes.
Add in your flour and mix well with your vegetable mix, and cook for 2 minutes. Next, add in tomato paste.
Add Short Ribs back into your Dutch oven (seared side up), and pour wine in. Turn heat up to a medium/high heat. Allow the alcohol to reduce for 3 minutes before adding in beef broth.
When adding beef broth, be sure that there is at least an inch of Short Ribs still above the liquid.
Add into oven for 4 hours on 300, they will literally fall off the bone and be soooo tender! Enjoy over creamy mashed potatoes.
Prep by cutting shallots, mincing your garlic, cutting your lemon slices, and parsley.
Cut Lobster Tails in half, and make sure your shrimp are nice and deveined.
Season your shrimp and lobster tails with the seasonings listed above.
Begin boiling your water, add salt, once boiling cook according to the packaging.
In a heated pan add in your olive oil and allow it to heat, add in your shrimp and allow them to cook for 2 minutes on each side. Add in 1 TBSP of your garlic herb butter and parsley.
Remove shrimp from pan and add in your lobster tails, allow it to cook for 3 minutes on each side, and add in your garlic herb butter.
Use 2/3 lemon slices and squeeze some lemon juice onto the lobster tails. Remove from pan once finished cooking.
In the same pan melt down 3 TBSP of butter, add in your shallots, parsley, and garlic until aromatic.
Add in your wine or chicken broth, and crushed red peppers. Cook for an additional 2 minutes.
Add in pasta water and lemon juice. Cook for an additional 3 minutes, and turn down the heat.
Add in your 3 TBSP of butter and add your noodles back in along with the shrimp and lobster tails.
Garnish with parsley and enjoy!
Season Chuck Roast with 1/2 TBSP of seasonings on both sides
Heat your dutch oven on a medium to high heat.
Once heated, add in 2 TBSP of Olive Oil
After olive oil is heated, add in your chuck roast and allow to sear on both sides for 4 minutes.
Add Ranch, Au Jux, and half of your onion soup packets.
Next add in your pepperoncini and beef broth.
Cover and cook on low to medium heat for 1.5 hours.
Add in butter on top of your chuck roast, cover and continue to cook for an additional hour.
Uncover and shred your chuck roast.
Serve with creamy mashed potatoes, white rice, and a refreshing veggie!
Slice pineapple down the middle and remove inside, for remaining pineapple use an ice cream scooper to get it all out.
Season your chicken with salt, pepper, garlic& onion powder.
Heat olive oil in a pan for 2/3 minutes before adding chicken. Cook chicken on medium to high heat 5/6 minutes on each side.
Remove chicken once at desired temp of 165, in same pan add in soy sauce and garlic. Turn heat down to a medium.
After garlic is aromatic, add in brown sugar and stir.  Mix cornstarch and water together before adding into sauce.
Allow sauce to cook for 2/3 minutes until thickened. Stirrring occasionally.
Once sauce is finished add chicken back in and allow to cook for 2 additional minutes.
Add rice to your pineapple bowl, chicken on top, and some extra sauce because you deserve it.
Enjoy!
Heat your oil in a pot or deep fryer, going for a temp of 350 degrees.
Season your chicken generously with every seasoning listed, about 1 TBSP of each seasoning should do the trick.
Add mustard on your chicken and give it all a really good mix. Make sure your chicken is seasoned very very generously.
Season your flour/corn startch mixture with the same seasonings: 1/2 TBSP each.
Dip your seasoned chicken into the mixture and make sure it is very well coated.
Add chicken into the oil and cook for 10-12 minutes, or until golden brown and the texture you desire.
Serve with your favorite side and enjoy!

ingredients.Name: Thinly Sliced Steak (your preferred slice, I used Ribeye)

directions.Direction: Prep work, slice your steak thinly, and slice your bell peppers and onions. Gather all of your ingredients, this will help with a quicker cooking process.
Season your steak with seasonings listed above, and get started on your white rice. For those who need help with white rice, I have a recipe listed in this book! 🙂
Heat olive oil in a pan, once this is heated, add in your steak and cook for about 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.

Remove from pan and add in your bell peppers, onion, and allow them to cook down. Season your veggies with salt and pepper. Add in your butter and allow them to cook. Total time for cooking veggies is about 4-5 minutes.

Add flour into the veggies, and mix well. It will look clumpy but that is okay, we’re making our gravy. Takes about 2 minutes for flour to cook through so add in your beef broth after 2 minutes of cooking flour.
Add in beef broth slowly and continously mix until gravy has thickened, it will be slightly watery but once you allow it to continue to cook it should be to your liking once finished.
Add in your steak and allow to cook for an additional 10 minutes. Serve with your white rice and enjoy!
In a heated pan, add olive oil and allow to heat, add in your andouille sausages and remove from heat once browned.
Add in celery, green bell pepper, and onion. Saute until softened and add in your pre soaked beans & mix well.
Add 5 Cups of of chicken broth, seasonings,  sausages, and your smoked turkey drumsticks.
Allow to cook on a low to medium heat for about an hour and half.
Remove turkey drumstick, shred, and add meat back to the pot.
Smash the beans against the side of the pot, this will give it that thickening texture. (Smash about 40% of the beans, it’s not necessasry to do all of them).
Cook for an additional 10 minutes and let cool.
Serve with white rice and cornbread!

ingredients.Name: Diced green bell pepper and onion
of the following: Creole, black pepper, onion powder, garlic powder

directions.Direction: Start by browning chicken thighs and andouille sausage.
Remove from pan and add flour and oil into same pan.
Mix well every 3 minutes until roux is desired darker color. (Takes 45 mins - 1 hour)
Add in bell pepper, celery, and onion. Cook for 5 minutes.
Add in chicken broth and seasonings and mix well.
Shred chicken and add in pot , along with sausage. Cook for 5 minutes.
Add in crab and shrimp. Cover and allow to simmer for additional 8 minutes.
Serve with rice and enjoy!

ingredients.Name: All Purpose Seasoning (my favorite is the Badia Complete Seasoning)

directions.Direction: Start by cutting your bacon into small pieces, and cleaning/cutting your chicken.
Season your chicken generously with the seasonings listed.
In a heated pan (medium to high heat), add pieces of your bacon into the pan and cook through, when bacon is finished, remove from the pan and set aside.
In the same pan, add in your seasoned chicken thighs and cook on each side for 4-5 minutes or until finished (internal temp of 165).
Cook your pasta according to the instructions provided on the back of the box.
Remove chicken from pan and set aside to rest.  Turn heat to a medium, add in minced garlic, and ranch seasoning. Mix well!
Add in heavy whipping cream, and allow to cook down for 4-5 minutes.
Once cooked down add in seasoning (1TSP) , cheese, cherry tomato, and spinach for about 5-6 minutes on a low heat. Stirring in between time.
Chop chicken after resting for about 5-10 minutes.
Add pasta into your sauce, chicken, and bacon. Mix until well combined, garnish with more bacon and some parsley!
Enjoy!
Start by seasoning your chicken generously with Dano’s Original, Dano’s Hot Seasoning and Salt.
In a heated pan, add olive oil and allow to heat. Once heated add chicken thighs in, skin side down and cook on each side for 4 minutes.
Your chicken will not be fully cooked at this point, it will cook throughout the recipe.
In the same pan add in your rice and allow to toast for 2/3 minutes.
Add in your chicken broth, and your chicken into the pan.
Cover and cook until rice is completed.
For the Sauce
Combine heavy whipping cream, danos, butter, and salt. Cook on a medium heat for 5 minutes.
Pour your sauce over your rice and chicken.
Allow rice to soak into the creamy sauce, serve and enjoy!
Preheat your oven to 400.
Slice your lemons.
Chop your parsley.
Mince your garlic.
Clean and devein your shrimp.
Season your shrimp with seasonings listed above, and drizzle olive oil on them.
Add garlic and parsley into your shrimp and mix well.
Line your shrimp in a pan and top with 4 TBSP of butter.
Bake for 15 minutes, remove from pan.
Serve & enjoy!

ingredients.Name: Garlic Cloves chopped to your liking

directions.Direction: Preparation is key to this recipe :) - Mince garlic and ginger.
-Get your broccoli cleaned and chopped into your preferred size.

To your sliced beef, add in 1/3 cup of soy sauce, salt, pepper, 1/2 of your ginger, 1/2 of your garlic, and baking powder (this acts as a meat tenderizer). Mix until well combined and allow to marinate for 20-30 minutes.
In a separate bowl combine the remaining soy sauce, ginger, garlic, 1 TBSP of seasame oil, your water, chicken broth, oyster sauce, rice wine vinegar, and season lightly. Mix until well combined.
Steam your broccoli during this time.
In a heated wok, add in 1 TBSP of oil. Allow this to heat before adding your meat in.
Allow your meat to get a good sear on both sides for about 3 minutes on each side. *Remove from pan and set aside, your meat will not be cooked throughly at this point*
In the same pan, pour your sauce, and allow to come to a boil, once sauce is thickened to your liking add in beef and broccoli.
Allow to cook for additional 5 minutes, serve on white rice. Garnish with seasame seeds, and enjoy!
Drizzle olive oil onto your salmon and season with seasonings listed on both the front and back of the salmon.
Heat a pan to a medium to high heat, with olive oil, once the pan is heated add your salmon in face down and cook for 4.5 minutes.
Flip your salmon and allow to cook for another 4-5 minutes.
Add in your sweet chili sauce and let it cook for another minute or so.
Plate and put your sauce on top, serve with your favorite sides and enjoy!

ingredients.Name: of the Smaller Chipotle Pepper Can
Tortillas of your choice (I did flour)

directions.Direction: Start by creating your chipotle cream sauce. Chipotle Cream Sauce: Blend Chipotle Peppers, mayo, the juice of one line, and sour cream.
Combine your green and red cabbage, cilantro, jalapeno, and tomato.
Add the juice of one lime and season lightly with salt and pepper.
Season your shrimp generously with chipotle seasoning and garlic pepper.
Heat a pan on a medium to high heat and add in a drizzle of olive oil.
Once olive oil has heated, add in your shrimp, be sure they are laying individually.
Cook for 3-4 minutes on each side, once finished, set aside and heat your tortillas.
Heat your tortillas and serve your shrimp and cabbage slaw, topped with the chipotle cream sauce. Serve & Enjoy!
Slice your steaks into even bite sized pieces and season well. Allow that to sit while you get your butter completed.
Use room temperature butter, add in chopped parsley, and garlic paste, season with a little salt and pepper. Combine until well incorporated.
Heat your pan on a high heat, add in avocado/olive oil, and allow this to get hot. You want to make sure your steak sizzles when you put it in. This will help with the sear of the steak.
Cook on each side for 3 minutes, and remove from the pan. This will be a medium well cook for the steak.
Add in your garlic herb butter and allow steak to cook inside of the pan for an additional 2 minutes.
Allow it to rest for at least 7-10 minutes, this allows it to contain the juices inside of the steak.
Serve and enjoy!
Start by prepping everything to help you get through this process faster. Cut andouille sausages into thick pieces, peel and devein your shrimp, and cut your corn into bite-sized pieces.
Preheat your oven to a temp of 400.
Boil your potaoes and corn for 10 minutes, add 1 TBSP of your Seafood Boil Seasoning Mix. This will help everything cook evenly in the end.
After your potatoes and corn cool off, build your seafood kabob. Assemble it however you see fit, add more of your favorites and less of what you don’t prefer.

Heat all of your butter and parsley together, season the butter to your tasting. Split your butter mixture in half, half will be for your seafood before it’s cooked. The other half for when it’s fully cooked. Brush 3 TBSP of the butter onto your kabobs.
Put your kabobs into the oven for 15 minutes and remove to rest. Brush the remaining butter mixture onto your kabobs or use it to dip!
This recipe can also be done on the grill as well
For the Compound Butter
Make our garlic compound butter. You combine your room temperature butter, minced garlic, chopped rosemary, thyme, and parsley. Season your butter with salt and butter.
Put your butter onto some plastic wrap and twist it until it is a circular shape.
Allow to refridgerate for at least an hour before using.
For the T-Bone Steak
Season your steak generously on both sides with salt and pepper.
Heat a cast iron with olive oil or avocado oil.
Once the oil has heated, add in your steak, and push steak down to help with an even sear.
Cook on each side for 3-4 minutes for a medium rare steak.
Add in 2 TBSP of your Garlic Compound butter, rosemary, thyme, and garlic.
Baste your steak for 30-45 seconds.
Remove steak and allow to rest for 8-10 minutes before slicing.

ingredients.Name: Of Gouda mozzarella and Parmesan cheese
One and a half cup of spinach

directions.Direction: Start by prepping your ingredients, grate your cheese, measure your spinach, and prep other food.
In a bowl combine your ricotta cheese, gouda, parmesean cheese, parsley, and spinach. Add in Oregano, Garlic Powder, Pepper, and Onion Powder.
Mix well until everything is combined, set in fridge.
Boil your lasagna noodles according to the packaging.
While noodles are boiling, heat a pan with olive oil, and add diced onion. Add in your ground turkey and cook until fully cooked.
Drain your meat and add back to pain. Add in marinara sauce and mix well.
Lay your lasgana noodles into a pan, add your ricotta cheese mixture into the inside of each noodle, followed by your meat/marinara sauce.
Roll the lasgna noodle tightly into a roll and place into a pan. Add enough to fill the entire pan, top with remaining marinara sauce, and more gouda cheese.
Garnish with parsley and place into oven for 15 minutes, or until golden brown. Allow to cool before serving! Enjoy!

ingredients.Name: Sauce:  cup soy sauce, 3 TBSP Oyster Sauce, 2 TSP sesame sauce, 1/4 cup chicken broth, 1/2 TBSP Sugar, 2 TSP White Pepper.

directions.Direction: Slice your chicken breasts into very thin strips.
Add 2 TSP Oyster Sauce, 1/2 of your minced garlic, cornstarch, 1 tbsp soy sauce, mix well and set aside to marinate while you prep your veggies.
Slice, Dice, or however you would like your veggies to be cooked. I sliced my cabbage and carrots thinly, feel free to add onions as well.
Make your sauce with remaining soy sauce, oyster sauce, 2 TSP sesame sauce, 1/4 cup chicken broth, 1/2 TBSP Sugar, 2 TSP White Pepper.
In a heated pan, add olive oil and allow to heat. Once hot add in your chicken and cook for about 4-5 minutes before adding in your veggies (cabbage, garlic, and carrots).
Add a splash of chicken broth, cover and let simmer on a low to medium heat.
As that finishes cooking, cook Lo Mein Noodles according to instructions on the back.
After 7 minutes, uncover chicken, add noodles, sauce and mix well.
Simmer for 5 minutes, serve and enjoy!
Prep everything to make this a super easy cook! Slice your veggies, cut the cabbage up, peel & devein shrimp, slice andouille sausages. Get seasonings out and ready for use! :)
Season shrimp generously with seasonings listed. I used about 1 TSP of each except the creole, did 2 TSP of that.
Start by heating a pan with some olive oil and brown your andouille sausages on both sides.
Remove from pan and turn heat down to a medium low, cook shrimp on both sides for 2 minutes. Remove shrimp and set aside.
Cook down your bell peppers and onions for 3/4 minutes on a medium heat before adding in cabbage.
Once cabbage has been added, add in your chicken broth, seasonings, and turn heat down to a low. (3/4 on knob). Cover cabbage and allow to simmer for 25 minutes, mixing in between time.
Once cabbage is the texture you desire add in sausage and shrimp!
Serve as a side or on a bed of white rice and enjoy! :)

ingredients.Name: of Olive Oil or Avocado Oil

directions.Direction: Prep everything first, cut your potatoes to size of your liking, slice your peppers and onion.
Boil your potatoes for about 15 minutes and then drain, once drained, season your potaotes with some all purpose seasoning or Dano’s Cheesoning.
Pre Heat oven to 375.
Season your steak very well on both sides, and heat your pan on a high heat.
Once the pan and oil has heated, add your steak and cook for 4 minutes on each side. Do not flip in between, let it get a really good sear on that steak.
Set aside and rest, this is a medium rare steak, if you like a different temp, continue to cook for an additional 2 mintues on each side.
Crack your eggs, season lightly with salt and pepper, add heavy whipping cream and mix very well.
Cook eggs on a low to medium heat, and once mostly done turn your heat off.
Put your potatoes in a skillet with the peppers and onion, slice your steak and place it on top, place your eggs, add cheese on top of eggs. Place it in the oven for about 5-7 minutes.
Garnish with green onion or parsley! Enjoy!

Peel your shrimp and place shell of shrimp into a small pot with chicken broth. This will create a more shrimp like broth for you to use for the sauce. Make sure you shrimp is nicely cleaned, and deveined. Boil on a medium high.
Prep all of the veggies, dice the bell peppers, slice your andouille sausages, and cook your bacon.
Season your shrimp, generously, and begin to boil your chicken broth for the grits.
Cook grits according to package/serving size. I prefer the 5 minute grits, do what you prefer. Be sure to add in grits just a little bit at a time, whisking while you are adding.
Once grits are mostly finished, add in your heavy whipping cream, cheese, and 2 TBSP of butter. Season with salt and pepper. Be sure to keep it on a medium to low heat.
In a pan on medium high heat, add in olive oil. Once that has heated add in your bell peppers, onion, and cook them until aromatic.

After 2-3 minutes add in your andouille sausage, and cook until they are brown or done to your liking. Go ahead and add in shrimp, cook on each side for 2.5 minutes. Be sure your shrimp is laying indivually and not clumped together.
Add in your 1/2 cup of the shrimp stock that you made, and your heavy whipping cream.
Allow to cook on a medium heat for about 2 minutes, add in some paprika for color.
Serve shrimp and sauce on top of your creamy grits, garnish with bacon bits and parsley. Enjoy!
Mix milk, egg, heavy whipping cream, vanilla extract, nutmeg, and cinnamon sugar into a bowl until well combined.
Heat a pan on a medium to low heat, add butter and allow it to melt.
Dip Hawaiian Roll into the mixture, do not completely soak it, just dip in on all sides.
Cook hawaiian roll for 1-2 minutes on each side, allowing to cook throughly.
Set aside, plate with strawberries, blackberries, and powdered sugar.
Enjoy!
Prep all of your ingredients prior to cooking, get seasonings out and accesible for the recipe.
Brown your ground beef, once half-way done, add in your onino, bell pepper, and season lightly with seasonings listed.
Drain beef and add into a pot, add in beans, tomato paste, diced tomato, and mix well.
Add in beef broth, mix well, and add in jalapeno for additional spice.
Season to your tasting and allow to simmer for an hour.
Taste, and enjoy! Serve with rice or cornbread.

ingredients.Name: of Grounded Italian Sausage (Hot or Mild, totally your preference)
(/2 TBSP crushed red pepper flakes, 1 TBSP for extra spice)

directions.Direction: Let’s prep! Chop your bacon into smaller bite sized pieces, dice your onion, mince your garlic, clean and cut your kale.
Heat Dutch oven or pot on a medium to high heat, add in bacon and cook bacon until crispy. Once bacon is crispy add in Italian sausage allow to brown.
Remove your Italian sausage once finished cooking/browning. Use a thick layer of paper towels to remove 3/4 of the grease at the bottom of the pot. (Keep some, this will help enhance flavors)
On a medium heat, add in your onion and garlic. Cook for 2 minutes before adding in seasonings listed above.
After cooking for 4 minutes, add in your chicken broth (if you don’t have any you can add water and 3 TBSP Chicken bouillon powder).
It’s time to add in our potatoes, if you did thicker chunks, allow to cook longer. If you did slices, cook down on a medium heat for about 7-10 minutes.
Add in your Italian sausage, bacon, and heavy cream to the pot. Cook down for 3 minutes.
Add in your clean, washed, cut kale.
Allow to simmer on a low to medium heat for an additional 5-7 minutes.
Serve and Enjoy!
Prep all of your ingredients, peel and dice your potatoes to the size of your liking. Place them into COLD water to prevent them from browning during the process.
Cut your bacon into small pieces and cook them in your pot until all the pieces are crispy. Remove from pan once finished and turn heat down to a low setting.
Add in your onion and green onion, cook down for 3 minutes and add in your flour.
After mixing well with onion & green onion, add in chicken broth, and your diced potatoes.
Cook for 5 minutes and add in heavy whipping cream, bacon, and cook for 20 minutes. Mixing well during the cook time. Once potatoes are tender turn off the heat.
Serve with grated cheese, bacon, and green onion as a garnish. Sour cream is also a great additive as well! Enjoy!
Clean your chicken, and remove any extra fat on the pieces.
Season with 1/2 TBSP of the seasonings listed above and drizzle 1/2 TBSP of Olive Oil. Mix chicken and seasonings really well.
Heat your pot on a medium to high heat, and add in your chicken once your oil has been heated.
Cook chicken on each side for about 5 minutes, once your chicken has fully cooked, remove and set aside to rest. Turn your heat down to a medium low heat.
In the same pan add in your butter, diced onion and garlic, and sun dried tomatoes. Cook down for 5 minutes and add in your chicken broth.
Add in your heavy whipping cream and cook for additional 5-6 minutes. While this is cooking, cut your chicken into bite sized pieces.
Once liquid is boiling, add in your seasonings, and mix well. Add in your grated parmesean and continue to cook.
Add in your gnocchi, spinach, and your chicken. Allow to cook for 5 minutes and turn off heat.
Serve and enjoy!

Make your chicken broth, you’re going to boil some water, add in your chicken breast, 1/2 of your onion, your celery, carrot, and 1/2 TBSP Salt, & 1 TBSP of Italian Seasoning. Boil on a medium to high heat for 25-30 minutes, or until Chicken reaches an internal temp of 165.
Use this time for prep, dice your onion, mince your garlic and get your remaining ingredients ready to go.
Remove Chicken Breast and 1 & 1/2 Cup of Chicken broth, the remaining can be stored in a Mason Jar for up to 7 days.
Shred your chicken, and set it aside. Pre-heat your oven to 385.
Heat a 12” Cast Iron Skillet or 12” Pan on a medium heat, add 3 TBSP of Butter.
After butter has melted, add in your diced onion, and garlic. Cook down for 2-3 minutes.
Sprinkle in your flour and mix until well combined, once combined and looking clumpy, add in chicken broth slowly and continue to mix.
After pouring in your chicken broth, add in your peas and carrots, cook down for 2 minutes, and add in heavy whipping cream, and your shredded chicken.
Season generously with seasonings listed and cook for 2/3 minutes.
Place your biscuits on top of the mixture, you can cut them into pieces as well if you would like. Place into the oven cook for 15 minutes or until golden brown.
While cooking, melt down 2 TBSP of butter. Once you take out your pot pie, brush the biscuits with butter and garnish with parsley.
Enjoy!

ingredients.Name: of Chocolate Chips/Baking Chips/ Chocolate Chunks

directions.Direction: Mix your brown and granulated sugar, with the softened butter until it’s fluffy.
Combine beaten eggs and vanilla extract together.
Combine dry ingredients together.
Sift your flour! (flour, salt, baking soda/powder).
Slowly mix in eggs into brown sugar/sugar.
Add/mix half the flour at a time.
Mix in chocolate chips/chunks.
Freeze cookie dough for up to 3 hours.
Bake on 350 for 12 minutes! Will look soft when they come out, but after they cool they will be PERFECT ❄️.

ingredients.Name: Hershey Cookies n Cream Candy Bars

directions.Direction: Mix butter until fluffy and add sugar/brown sugar and mix.
Combine Eggs and Vanilla Extract
Add slowly to the butter and sugar mixture.
Combine dry ingredients and whisk
Add in dry ingredients to Egg and Butter mixture
Mix until it’s thick and chop Hersheys & Oreos.
Fold in chopped Oreo and candy.
Chill for 30 minutes.
Form into medium sized balls and cook on 350 for 10 minutes.
Allow to cool and ENJOY!!
Cook sliced peaches with nut meg, cinnamon, and sugar.
Mix softened butter with room temp cream cheese until well blended and soft and begins to peak.
Add in sugar and mix well, beat your eggs separately before adding in very slowly. Mix well after every time you add in eggs.
Mix dry ingredients and add in slowly.
Spray pan with non stick spray very well and line with cooked peaches.
Pour cake batter on top of the peaches and bake for 2 hours on 335.
